<br>
The major thing to remember about the tanking debate is at higher levels the damage output of the main tank is a secondary concern at best.  Eventually it becomes a very, very distant second at raiding level.  The only major reason a main tank needs to deal more damage at the high end is to generate more agro, since holding agro becomes everything.  Literally everything.  Well, that and being able to survive agro. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The life of a professional tank is a good one.  I've done it, as a paladin, and if I had it to do over, based on game mechanics, I'd try it as a Shadowknight because I love pulling also.  I was disappointed when I had to stop pulling as a Paladin. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Rest assured, Warriors are not under-appreciated.  There are a lot on FV, and there's room for more.  90% of the time, assuming roughly equal levels and equipment, a warrior will lead tank over anyone else.  And you get to do interesting things like Master Loot a lot, because you've got lots of strength and no need to meditate.<br>
<br>
Whichever you choose, you'll have fun and there will always be folks to group with.  Don't obsess over what's better too much.  It's been hashed, rehashed, rerehash etc.  The classes are probably as balanced now as they are ever going to be or ever could be, and all have their strengths and weaknesses.  Play whatever seems like fun.<br>
<br>
Valquiss <p><img src=http://www.traveling.freehosting.net/valquisssig2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/17/02 11:17:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Warriors vs Paladins</span><hr size=1> Two words: Defensive Discipline<br>
<br>
Here's the bottom line: If you want to be essential to the success of a high level raid, you play a warrior. Without *real* tanks, a lot of high level encounters simply aren't doable. As much as I love being a Shadowknight, and as much as I admire and respect the Paladin class, there is no substitute for a pure warrior. <br>
<br>
But really, it only makes a difference at the end-game. Until you reach that point, level 55-60, it doesn't matter. <br>
<br>
If you have no intentions of reaching those levels, and being a part of those raids, then play whatever makes you happy. <br>
<br>
Oh.. and about the weapon thing: Warriors get a LOT more weapons, and have a lot more choices.. give it time. <br>
<br>
